parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure due to Sludge Buildup
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause the vehicle to stall or cease functioning, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine may produce a knocking or tapping noise
and the check engine light may come on. The vehicle may stall or die while driving
and the engine may eventually seize.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the air conditioner can cause discomfort and distraction while driving.
symptoms: The air conditioner may stop working
blowing warm air instead of cold.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission problems can cause the vehicle to stall or hesitate, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle may hesitate or jerk when shifting gears
or the transmission may slip or fail to engage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cooling system failure can cause the engine to overheat, leading to damage or failure.
symptoms: The vehicle may overheat
and the temperature gauge may rise into the red zone.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failures can cause a range of problems, including stalling, loss of power, and malfunctioning accessories.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience electrical system malfunctions
such as faulty wipers
lights
or accessories.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clutch and transmission problems can cause the vehicle to stall or hesitate, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The clutch pedal may feel soft or spongy
or the vehicle may jerk or hesitate when shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ball joint can cause the wheel to become detached from the vehicle, leading to loss of control and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The ball joint breaks or separates from the lower control arm
causing the wheel to lean or fall off
and resulting in loss of steering control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the lower control arm can cause the wheel to become detached from the vehicle, leading to loss of control and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The lower control arm fractures or breaks
causing the wheel to lean or fall off
and resulting in loss of steering control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear strut mount can cause the strut to wear through the inside sidewall of the tire, leading to a blowout and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The rear strut mount corrodes and fails
causing a rattling noise and potentially leading to a blowout.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbags to deploy in a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The airbag light comes on
the airbag warning light blinks
the airbag deploys unnecessarily
or the airbag fails to deploy in a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The airbag light illumination can indicate a faulty airbag system, which can lead to airbag failure or unnecessary deployment.
symptoms: The airbag light comes on
the airbag warning light blinks
or the airbag light stays on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The airbag system malfunction can lead to airbag failure or unnecessary deployment, which can cause injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The airbag deploys unnecessarily
the airbag fails to deploy in a crash
or the airbag system malfunctions.
